seasons.title: Great Raids of World War II

episodes.synopsis: A team of Norwegian raiders keeps an A-bomb ingredient from the Germans by destroying a factory.
episodes.title: Stopping Hitler's A-Bomb

episodes.synopsis: French Resistance operatives are freed from Amiens Prison through exacting targeted bombing of the prison walls by the Mosquito fighter-bomber.
episodes.title: Prison Busters

episodes.synopsis: The British capture a German radar installation that is key to the Nazi air-defense system.
episodes.title: Radar Beam Raiders

episodes.synopsis: The mission of the destroyer HMS Campbeltown is to destroy the only dock large enough to repair Germany's giant battleship Tirpitz.
episodes.title: Storm at St. Nazaire

episodes.synopsis: A special force in canoes tries to clog the flow of Nazi supplies moving through Bordeaux, France.
episodes.title: Cockleshell Raiders

episodes.synopsis: A British commando assault on Vaagso, Norway, in December 1941 dupes Hitler into committing and ultimately wasting 250,000 Nazi troops.
episodes.title: Arctic Commando Assault

video.title: Great Raids of World War II
video.synopsis: This series presents six stories of small-scale Allied military operations told through the accounts of World War II veterans and archival footage.
